{"entity": "Patient Guide", "type": "content", "description": "The term \"Patient Guide\" refers to distinct informational resources, each focused on a specific medical condition. Based on the provided descriptions, there are three separate guides.\n\nOne Patient Guide is dedicated to **squamous cell skin cancer**. This resource is a document focused exclusively on this condition and uses the terms \"squamous cell skin cancer\" and \"CSCC\" (cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma) interchangeably.\n\nAnother Patient Guide addresses **cervical cancer**. This document provides comprehensive information on the disease, including its common types, risk factors, and treatment options. It explicitly notes that it does not cover rarer cervical cancer variants such as glassy-cell carcinomas and sarcomas.\n\nA third Patient Guide is a book focused on **chronic lymphocytic leukemia/small lymphocytic lymphoma (CLL/SLL)**. It is described as a comprehensive resource for living with CLL, covering essential topics such as diagnostic tests, available treatment options, and supportive care strategies."}
