{"entity": "High-Risk Tumors", "type": "concept", "description": "High-risk tumors are a category of CSCC for which adjuvant radiation therapy may be used after surgery to prevent recurrence.<SEP>High-risk tumors are cancers that have a greater chance of returning, sometimes requiring adjuvant radiation therapy.<SEP>High-risk tumors are cancers that have a greater chance of returning, sometimes requiring adjuvant radiation therapy.<SEP>Tumors considered high risk due to location and/or size, including those on trunk, arms, or legs between 2 cm and 4 cm, and any size tumor on head, face, neck, hands, feet, shins, or sex organs."}
