{"entity": "Actinic Keratoses", "type": "concept", "description": "Actinic keratoses are pre-cancerous skin lesions characterized by scaly or rough patches. They are primarily caused by prolonged exposure to the sun. If left untreated, these lesions have the potential to develop into squamous cell carcinoma, a form of skin cancer.\n\nThe management of actinic keratoses typically involves superficial treatments aimed at removing the damaged cells. Common and effective treatment options include cryotherapy (freezing), photodynamic therapy, and various topical therapies."}
