{"entity": "Weakened Immune System", "type": "concept", "description": "A weakened immune system is a condition characterized by an impaired or reduced ability of the body to fight infections and diseases. This state of immunosuppression is a significant and broad health risk factor, substantially increasing susceptibility to various cancers.

