{"entity": "AIDS", "type": "concept", "description": "Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome (AIDS) is a serious condition caused by infection with the Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV). The disease results in a profound weakening of the immune system, a state known as immunodeficiency. This compromised immune function significantly increases an individual's susceptibility to various opportunistic infections and specific cancers.

