{"entity": "Actinic Keratoses", "type": "concept", "description": "Actinic keratoses are pre-cancerous skin lesions characterized by scaly or rough patches. They are primarily caused by prolonged exposure to the sun. If left untreated, these lesions have the potential to develop into squamous cell carcinoma, a form of skin cancer.

The management of actinic keratoses typically involves superficial treatments aimed at removing the damaged cells. Common and effective treatment options include cryotherapy (freezing), photodynamic therapy, and various topical therapies."}
{"entity": "Immune System", "type": "concept", "description": "The immune system is the body's complex, natural defense system against infection and disease. It functions as a bodily system that includes the lymphatic system and its components, such as specialized cells like lymphocytes. A key function is to defend the body by recruiting antibodies and other mechanisms to fight pathogens like viruses and bacteria, including the clearance of certain viral infections such as human papillomavirus (HPV).

Consequently, an impaired or weakened immune system—which can result from conditions like HIV/AIDS or certain medical treatments—significantly increases susceptibility to infections and various cancers. Specific associated risks include squamous cell skin cancer, anal cancer (due to hindered HPV clearance), and primary CNS lymphoma. Furthermore, certain cancers, like acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL), originate in immune cells like lymphocytes.

In medical treatment, the immune system itself is a therapeutic target. Immunotherapy works by utilizing or activating this defense system to find and destroy cancer cells. Specific approaches include BCG therapy, which triggers the immune system to attack cancer cells inside the bladder, and checkpoint inhibitor therapy, which is designed to enhance the immune system's inherent ability to fight cancer.<SEP>The immune system can get rid of or "clear" HPV from the body in most people.<SEP>The Immune System is the broader bodily system of which the Lymphatic System is a part.<SEP>The Immune System is the body's natural defense against infection and disease; an impaired immune system increases the risk of Primary CNS Lymphoma."}
