{"entity": "Skin Exam", "type": "method", "description": "A skin exam is a specific type of physical examination performed by a doctor or healthcare provider that is focused entirely on the patient's skin. Its primary purpose is to identify concerning lesions. This procedure serves multiple diagnostic and monitoring roles. It is a standard follow-up method to check for the recurrence of skin cancers, such as squamous cell carcinoma and basal cell carcinoma, after treatment, and to screen for signs of new skin cancers.

