{"entity": "Lesion", "type": "concept", "description": "A lesion is a broad medical term referring to an area of abnormal tissue, most commonly described as an area of dysplasia or cancer, indicating a deviation from normal, healthy cellular structure. It represents a localized site of pathology requiring medical evaluation or intervention and is applied across various medical contexts to denote the specific site of disease.

