{"entity": "Skin Biopsy", "type": "method", "description": "A skin biopsy is a diagnostic medical procedure in which a small sample of skin tissue is removed for laboratory analysis. It is the definitive method for diagnosing various skin conditions, most notably skin cancers. The procedure is most frequently described in two distinct clinical contexts.

In the primary and most common context of general dermatology, a skin biopsy involves removing a sample of a suspicious skin lesion. This sample is sent to a laboratory for examination by a pathologist to confirm or rule out skin cancer. The procedure is repeatedly cited as the definitive diagnostic method for squamous cell skin cancer, not only confirming its presence but also helping to determine its specific type and characteristics.

