{"entity": "Local CSCC", "type": "concept", "description": "Local CSCC, which stands for Local Cutaneous Squamous Cell Carcinoma (also commonly referred to as squamous cell skin cancer), is a form of skin cancer that is confined to its original site. It is specifically defined by the absence of spread, or metastasis, to nearby lymph nodes. In some descriptions, this local confinement is further clarified as cancer that has not spread beyond the original site.

