{"entity": "Clear Cell RCC", "type": "concept", "description": "Clear Cell Renal Cell Carcinoma (Clear Cell RCC or ccRCC) is the most common subtype of renal cell carcinoma (RCC). It accounts for approximately 70% (or about 7 out of 10) of all RCC cases. The defining histological characteristic of this cancer, visible under a microscope, is the presence of tumor cells with a pale or clear cytoplasm."}
