{"entity": "Low-Risk CSCC", "type": "concept", "description": "Low-Risk CSCC (cutaneous squamous cell carcinoma) is a classification of squamous cell skin cancer determined through risk assessment based on key features of the cancer. It is characterized by a lower likelihood of recurrence and metastasis compared to high-risk disease, specifically referring to tumors that have not spread to lymph nodes. Due to this more favorable prognosis, it is treated differently from high-risk CSCC. The preferred and primary treatment is surgery, with specific surgical and radiation treatment protocols recommended for this category.<SEP>Low-risk CSCC is a category of squamous cell skin cancer with a lower risk of recurrence and metastasis."}
